Drones expend energy to fight gravity and to counter drag forces due to forward motion and wind. The drone’s control software adjusts the speed of each rotor to achieve the thrust and pitch necessary to stay aloft and travel forward at the desired velocity. On average, the thrusts from each of the rotors are roughly equal and together exactly balance gravity and drag forces. We can then find the total required thrust by:1T=mbody+mbatt+mpackageg+Fdrag,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
