				\begin{document}$$T = \left( {m_{{\mathrm{body}}} + m_{{\mathrm{batt}}} + m_{{\mathrm{package}}}} \right)g + F_{{\mathrm{drag}}},$$\end{document}where mbody, mbatt, and mpackage are the masses of the drone body, battery, and package (if present), g is the gravitational constant, and Fdrag is the total drag force. Similarly, for steady flight, the pitch angle, α, can be calculated by:2α=tan-1Fdragmbody+mbatt+mpackageg.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
